          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>529 Expansion and Modernization Act of 2018 </b></p> <p>This bill allows tax-exempt distributions from qualified tuition programs (known as 529 plans) to be used for: </p> <ul> <li> apprenticeship programs, </li> <li> early education expenses for children under the age of 5, </li> <li> career and technical education programs, and </li> <li> industry intermediary education programs.</li> </ul> <p>The bill also allows employers to make contributions to an employee's 529 plan as a fringe benefit that is excluded from the gross income of the employee. The contributions per employee may not exceed $500 per year (adjusted for inflation after 2019) and must be made in connection with a payroll deduction contribution program.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-07-17T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-03-25T19:58:19Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
